					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">What happens if you treat all transparent colors as transparent black and then use premultiplied alpha?</div><br /><br />In that case it will give the correct result:<br />A = (A1 + A2) / 2<br />R = (R1 * A1 + R2 * A2) / (A1 + A2) = (pR1 + pR2) / (A1 + A2)<br />G = (G1 * A1 + G2 * A2) / (A1 + A2) = (pG1 + pG2) / (A1 + A2)<br />B = (B1 * A1 + B2 * A2) / (A1 + A2) = (pB1 + pB2) / (A1 + A2)<br />pR = R * A = (pR1 + pR2) / 2<br />pG = G * A = (pG1 + pG2) / 2<br />pB = B * A = (pB1 + pB2) / 2</div>

